            <h2><a href="http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/blogs/earthmatters/2013/09/20/september-puzzler-answer-chara-sands/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to September Puzzler Answer: Chara Sands">September Puzzler Answer: Chara Sands</a></h2>
            <span class="date">September 20th, 2013  by Adam Voiland</span>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section">
            <p>Congratulations to <a href="http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/blogs/earthmatters/2013/09/16/september-puzzler-2/#comment-12670">Felix Bossert</a> for being the quickest to solve the <a href="http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/blogs/earthmatters/2013/09/16/september-puzzler-2/?src=earthmatters-rss">September puzzler.</a> The answer is the Chara Sands.  See the <a href="http://www.earthobservatory.nasa.gov/IOTD/view.php?id=82112&amp;eocn=home&amp;eoci=iotd_grid">Image of the Day</a> that published on September 21, 2013, for a second image and details about the area. Also congratulations to <a href="http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/blogs/earthmatters/2013/09/16/september-puzzler-2/#comment-12738">Robert Emberson</a> for providing interesting details about the geologic history of the dunes.</p>
<p>It only took Bossert a few hours to get the answer<b>—</b>impressive because we hadn&#8217;t even promoted the puzzler through our <a href="http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/Subscribe/">email newsletter,</a> <a href="https://www.facebook.com/NASAEarthObservatory">Facebook page,</a> or <a href="https://twitter.com/NASA_EO">Twitter feed.</a> I can&#8217;t say I&#8217;m surprised because Felix is a veteran of the geology puzzler <a href="http://woge-felix.blogspot.com/p/rules-of-geological-whereongoogleearth.html">Where on Google Earth</a> (WOGE).  Give WOGE a try, but make sure <a href="http://woge-felix.blogspot.com/p/rules-of-geological-whereongoogleearth.html">know the rules </a>and be prepared to host the next WOGE if you win.)</p>
<p><a href="http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/blogs/earthmatters/files/2013/09/charasands_oli_2013192.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-3968" alt="charasands_oli_2013192" src="http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/blogs/earthmatters/files/2013/09/charasands_oli_2013192.jpg" width="720" height="480" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="section">
            <p class="postmetadata"> Posted in <a href="http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/blogs/earthmatters/category/eos-satellite-puzzler/" rel="category tag">EO's Satellite Puzzler</a> |   <a href="http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/blogs/earthmatters/2013/09/20/september-puzzler-answer-chara-sands/#comments" title="Comment on September Puzzler Answer: Chara Sands">1 Comment so far</a></p>

        </div>
            
